but total emptiness.

49:22.226 --> 49:24.427
And just really wanting to find
the quickest way out the door.

49:24.429 --> 49:27.596
All for what?
A couple of hours of pleasure?

49:27.598 --> 49:30.099
- Or we could end up dating.

49:30.101 --> 49:33.302
And then, after a few months--

49:33.304 --> 49:36.505
good months, where our feet
never touch the floor--

49:37.742 --> 49:40.676
Maybe we don't want to invest
in this, you know?

49:40.678 --> 49:42.511
How much do we want to
invest in this thing--

49:42.513 --> 49:43.846
- Yeah.
- --That's taken time away

49:43.848 --> 49:45.915
from meeting someone else?

49:45.917 --> 49:48.851
Maybe I decide
that I wanna move on.

49:48.853 --> 49:50.886
- Well--
- Only to realize of course

49:50.888 --> 49:55.291
that, "Oh no,
that was really great."

49:55.293 --> 49:58.027
- Or maybe I'm the one
agonizing--

49:58.029 --> 49:59.395
--over my exit strategy

49:59.397 --> 50:01.931
because I'm-- I'm somehow
riddled with all this guilt

50:01.933 --> 50:06.002
over telling you that,
"I'm really sorry,

50:06.004 --> 50:08.604
but this isn't
gonna happen after all."

50:08.606 --> 50:12.108
- Oh!
So I'm left there wondering--

50:12.110 --> 50:14.677
--did I mismanage my emotions

50:14.679 --> 50:16.412
when I was with you?

50:16.414 --> 50:17.480
If I had done this
or that differently--

50:17.482 --> 50:19.181
- Agh!

50:19.183 --> 50:20.716
Yes.
- --Would you have left me?!

50:20.718 --> 50:22.852
- The pining
is the fucking worst!

50:22.854 --> 50:25.488
It's true.

50:25.490 --> 50:27.356
- It's pretty fucking awful.

50:27.358 --> 50:28.357
- Yeah.

50:29.894 --> 50:34.330
So why not just stick yourself
in a foxhole

50:34.332 --> 50:35.831
with someone
we're comfortable with,

50:35.833 --> 50:39.235
who cares for you,
fulfills all your daily needs--

50:39.237 --> 50:40.169
- Hmm.

50:40.171 --> 50:41.871
- --Even though
you're not entirely sure

50:41.873 --> 50:43.472
that they're the one.

50:49.047 --> 50:50.046
- Wow.

50:51.049 --> 50:52.848
